A Buhari/Osinbajo solidarity group, Noble Women Movement for Buhari and Osinbajo (NWM4BO), has commended INEC for conducting free, fair and credible elections. The women group also commended Nigerians across the six geopolitical zones for the massive support in the re-election of President Muhammadu Buhari and Vice President Prof. Yemi Osinbajo in the just concluded 2019 presidential and National Assembly elections. Addressing a press conference, yesterday in Abuja, the group’s National President, Mrs. Mfawa Usani and Director of Publicity, Dr. Rachael Ahmadu, commended the transparency exhibited by the electoral body before and during the elections, stressing that INEC recorded great improvements in the 2019 elections when compared to 2015 and other previous elections Usani, also expressed gratitude to God for the relatively peaceful elections. FCT: No blackmail against Buhari will work - Women Buhari solidarity group wants women to vote wisely Buhari not losing sleep over alliance — Women group